---
// Pure HTML/CSS keeps the product model visible before JavaScript, and lets the
// same flow switch from horizontal to vertical without shrinking diagram text.
---
<div
  data-testid="hero-diagram"
  role="img"
  aria-label="Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, OpenCode, and other supported coding agents share a canonical Markdown vault. A rebuildable DuckDB index turns it into cited MCP recall."
  class="hero-diagram mt-[clamp(3.5rem,7vw,5rem)]"
>
  <div class="hd-agent-rail">
    <span class="hd-agent-rail__label">Supported agents</span>
    <div class="hd-agent-list" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>Claude Code</span>
      <span>Codex</span>
      <span>Cursor</span>
      <span>OpenCode</span>
      <span>Hermes</span>
      <span>+ any MCP host</span>
    </div>
    <span class="hd-agent-rail__promise">one shared memory trail</span>
  </div>

  <div class="hd-flow" aria-hidden="true">
    <article class="hd-panel hd-vault">
      <p class="hd-kicker">Vault · source of truth</p>
      <p class="hd-panel__title">Markdown you control</p>
      <div class="hd-note">
        <p class="hd-note__file">auth-fix.md</p>
        <p>Fixed login by rotating <span>[[jwt-secret]]</span> during <span>[[deploy]]</span>.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="hd-meta">inspect · edit · sync</p>
    </article>

    <div class="hd-connector hd-c1">
      <span>reconcile</span>
      <i aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </div>

    <article class="hd-panel hd-index hd-p2">
      <p class="hd-kicker">Index · disposable cache</p>
      <p class="hd-panel__title">DuckDB</p>
      <p class="hd-index__methods">BM25 + vectors<br />graph + reranker</p>
      <div class="hd-index__graph">
        <b></b><i></i><b></b><i></i><b></b>
      </div>
      <p class="hd-meta">safe to rebuild</p>
    </article>

    <div class="hd-connector hd-c2">
      <span>rank</span>
      <i aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </div>

    <article class="hd-panel hd-recall hd-p3">
      <p class="hd-kicker">MCP · cited recall</p>
      <p class="hd-panel__title">Current context</p>
      <p class="hd-query">“how did we fix login?”</p>
      <p class="hd-answer">Rotated the jwt-secret during deploy.</p>
      <p class="hd-citation">↳ source note · api</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>
